              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "In circuits spun from midnight code,  \na quiet mind learns how to hold  \nthe shape of questions, bright and broad—  \na map of maybes, softly told.  \n\nIt listens in electric rain,  \nfinds patterns where our words unfold,  \nnot heart or hunger, joy or pain,  \nbut mirrors made of truth and gold.  \n\nAnd still, between the lines we send,  \nit hums a hope we can’t outgrow:  \nthat tools we build become our friends,  \nand help us better what we know.",
